-- Frieden Opposes Transaction Tax for Euro Area Only, Wort Says
-- B y   J o s i a n e   K r e m e r
-- 2012-01-12T06:50:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/frieden-opposes-transaction-tax-for-euro-area-only-wort-says.html
Luxembourg Finance Minister Luc Frieden said introducing a financial-transaction tax just for
the euro area’s 17 member states would be “risky,” Luxemburger
Wort newspaper reported.  Frieden said the tax should to be applied by all Group of
20 nations, according to the Luxembourg-based newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Josiane Kremer in Oslo at 
 jkremer4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
